{{h1}}Git Commit

{{h2}}Branching

- Check the current branch before committing
  - If on `main`, create and switch to a feature branch with a descriptive name based on the current change
    Use a feature/ prefix for new or updated features, bugfix/ prefix for bug fixes etc.
  - If you are not on `main`, continue on the current branch unless there is a clear reason to branch differently
- Review the current changes and create an appropriate commit message that reflects the actual change
- Only describe the changes, no statistics, no specific filenames, etc.

{{h2}}Instructions

- Use {{#resource}}commit{{/resource}} to prepare the commit message
- Unless otherwise directed, stage only the intended files
- Create a single commit for the current logical change unless the work clearly needs to be split
- Do not amend existing commits:
  - Unless explicitly requested
  - if a commit has already been pushed
